text: IIona Zádor was a female Hungarian international table tennis player. ==Table tennis career== She won a bronze medal at the 1929 World Table Tennis Championships in the women's doubles with Magda Gál. ==Personal life== She was of Jewish descent. ==See also== * List of table tennis players * List of World Table Tennis Championships medalists ==References== Category:Hungarian female table tennis players Category:World Table Tennis Championships medalists
title: IIona Zádor
